  "prompt": "How do you use Google Account Recovery to reset your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Google account password and need to reset it, you can use Google Account Recovery to regain access. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do it:\n\n1. **Go to Google Account Recovery:**\n   - Visit the Google Account Recovery page at `https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery`.\n\n2. **Enter Your Email Address:**\n   - Input the email address for the Google account you are trying to recover and click \"Next.\"\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Google will present several verification options to confirm your identity. These might include:\n     - Receiving a verification code via SMS or a voice call to your registered phone number.\n     - Using a secondary email address associated with your account.\n     - Answering specific security questions that you previously set up.\n     - Using a trusted device where you were previously signed in.\n\n4. **Follow the Instructions:**\n   - Choose the verification method you have access to and follow the on-screen instructions. You may need to enter a verification code or answer security questions.\n\n5. **Create a New Password:**\n   - Once your identity is verified, you will be prompted to set a new password. Make sure your new password is strong and secure. It should be at least 8 characters long and include a mix of upper and lower case letters, numbers, and symbols.\n\n6. **Recovery Confirmation:**\n   - After setting your new password, you will receive a confirmation that your password has been reset. You can now use this new password to sign in to your Google account.\n\n7. **Update Recovery Information:**\n   - It's a good idea to update your recovery options (like phone number and recovery email) to ensure you can recover your account easily in the future.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, make sure to follow the on-screen instructions carefully, as Google may offer additional options based on your account setup and history. If you are unable to recover your account, consider visiting Google\u2019s Help Center or contacting their support for further assistance.",
